 staff  the cadets spent their time at nursing homes  churches  local residences  and farms  lending a helping hand and enriching lives of senior citizens  Cadets also volunteered at the Virginia Horse Center  Habitat for Humanity  and Project Horizon  an organization dedicated to helping victims of domestic violence and sexual assault  Each year Air Force ROTC cadets plan and execute a series of community service events in and around Lexington  The impact of these activities on the local community is significant  as is the pride that each cadet feels in taking advantage of the opportunity to do something for the community and for those who are in need of help  By  AF ROTC IR   Nov  2014 VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 